HEADWORD: Confectioner
<hw>Con*fec"tion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
compounder.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Canidia Neapolitana was <qex>confectioner</qex> of unguents.</q>
<rj><qau>Haywood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One whose occupation it is to make or sell
confections, candies, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confectioners' sugar</ent>⟦br⟧
